A YouTube content creator has unveiled a list of countries he believes harbour the most unfaithful married women in the world. In a video posted by the Nigerian entertainment blog GHpage, the YouTuber ranked the most populous African country as one that holds the crown on that front. He said Nigeria leads the pack of eight countries in his list with 62 per cent of women having confirmed cheating once or multiple times on their partners. He listed Thailand in second place with 59 per cent, the UK came third with 42 per cent, Malaysia fourth (39%), Russia fifth (33%) and Singapore sixth with 19 per cent. According to the content creator, France is the second least country in the group of eight where only 16 per cent of women confirmed cheating on their partners while the US had 14 per cent.